 Three men, clad in gloves and balaclavas assaulted Mr Markram with pangas during the attack. Mr Markram’s hand was split open during the assault and both he and his daughter were rushed to Midmed Hospital for treatment.
They were discharged on the same day. Also read: BREAKING NEWS: Another farm attack – three suspects still on the loose In a description of the attackers, it was said that the one man was short in build and was wearing a pair of light blue trousers and a green shirt. The second attacker was described as slightly taller and was wearing a red jacket with black trousers and carrying a blue backpack. The third man was a tall, older man also wearing a red jacket. Members of the community formed a search party for the suspects until the SAPS took over with an ongoing investigation. •Read full article in the Middelburg Observer.  R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za  